# LATERALUS Quick Reference Card

A concise reference for all language features, syntax, and built-in functions.

## Variable Declaration

```lateralus
let x = 42              // Mutable binding
let name = "LATERALUS"  // Type-inferred string
let pi = 3.14159        // Float literal
let active = true       // Boolean
let empty = none        // None/null
```

## Functions

```lateralus
fn add(a: int, b: int) -> int {
    return a + b
}

// Single-expression functions
fn double(x: int) -> int { x * 2 }

// Anonymous functions (lambdas)
let square = fn(x) { x * x }
```

## Pipeline Operators

```lateralus
// Standard pipeline
let result = data |> map(fn(x) { x * 2 }) |> filter(fn(x) { x > 5 }) |> sum

// Optional pipeline (safe None propagation)
let safe = maybe_value |? map(fn(x) { x + 1 }) |? unwrap_or(0)
```

## Control Flow

```lateralus
// If/else
if condition {
    // ...
} else if other {
    // ...
} else {
    // ...
}

// Match expressions
let label = match status {
    200 => "OK",
    404 => "Not Found",
    500 => "Server Error",
    _ => "Unknown",
}

// Loops
for item in collection {
    println(item)
}

while condition {
    // ...
}
```

## Error Handling

```lateralus
// Throw exceptions
throw ValueError("Invalid input")

// Try-catch
try {
    risky_operation()
} catch e {
    println("Error: " + str(e))
}

// Try as expression
let result = try parse(input) catch "default"
```

## Result & Option Types (v1.5)

```lateralus
// Result<T, E> — explicit success or failure
fn safe_div(a: float, b: float) -> Result<float, str> {
  if b == 0.0 { return Result::Err("division by zero") }
  return Result::Ok(a / b)
}

// Option<T> — value or nothing (no null)
fn find(id: int) -> Option<str> {
  if id == 1 { return Option::Some("root") }
  return Option::None
}

// :: scope operator accesses constructors
let ok = Result::Ok(42)
let err = Result::Err("not found")
let some = Option::Some("hello")
let none = Option::None

// Match as expression with ADT destructuring
let msg = match safe_div(10.0, 3.0) {
  Result::Ok(v) if v > 5  => "large: {v}",
  Result::Ok(v)            => "result: {v}",
  Result::Err(e)           => "error: {e}",
}

// Pattern types: literal, binding, wildcard,
// constructor, guard, OR, list, nested
let weekend = match day {
  "Saturday" | "Sunday" => true,
  _                      => false,
}
```

## Hindley-Milner Type Inference (v1.5)

```lateralus
// Types are inferred — no explicit annotations needed
let x = 42               // inferred: int
let name = "LATERALUS"    // inferred: str
let result = safe_div(1.0, 2.0)  // inferred: Result<float, str>

// Robinson unification resolves type constraints
// Occurs check prevents infinite types
// Pattern-aware inference handles all 8 pattern types
```

## Optional Types (v1.5)

```lateralus
// Append ? to any type to make it optional (nullable)
let name: str? = nil          // str? accepts str or nil
fn find(id: int) -> map? {    // may return nil
    if id == 0 { return nil }
    return {id: id}
}

// Type narrowing after nil checks
let user: map? = find(1)
if user != nil {
    // user is narrowed to map (non-optional) here
    println(user["id"])
}
```

## Generics with Trait Bounds (v1.5)

```lateralus
// Plain generics
fn identity<T>(x: T) -> T { return x }

// Trait-bounded generics
fn sort<T: Comparable>(items: list) -> list { ... }

// Multiple bounds
fn display<T: Show, U: Eq>(a: T, b: U) { ... }

// Const generics for value-level parameters
struct Matrix<N: int, M: int> {
    data: list,
    rows: int,
    cols: int,
}
```

## C Backend (v1.5)

```lateralus
// Transpile to C99 with the CLI
// lateralus c program.ltl -o program.c
// lateralus c kernel.ltl --freestanding -o kernel.c

// Supported C targets:
//   Hosted    — links libc, stdio, stdlib
//   Freestanding — no libc, custom heap, for OS kernels
```

```lateralus
struct Point {
    x: float,
    y: float,
}

interface Printable {
    fn to_string() -> str
}

let p = Point { x: 3.0, y: 4.0 }
```

## Decorators

```lateralus
@memo                     // Memoization cache
fn fibonacci(n: int) -> int { ... }

@test                     // Mark as test case
fn test_math() { assert_eq(2 + 2, 4) }

@typed                    // Runtime type checking
fn safe_add(a: int, b: int) -> int { a + b }
```

## Comprehensions & Guards (v1.4)

```lateralus
// List comprehension with filter
let squares = [x ** 2 for x in range(10) if x % 2 == 0]

// Set and map comprehensions
let unique = {x for x in data if x > 0}
let lookup = {k: v for k, v in pairs}

// Guard clause — early exit
fn process(data: List<int>) -> int {
  guard len(data) > 0 else { return 0 }
  return data |> sum()
}

// Ternary expression
let label = x > 0 ? "positive" : "non-positive"

// Spread operator
let all = [0, ...items, 99]

// Pipeline-assign
data |>= sort()
```

## Event System

```lateralus
// Emit events
emit "user_login" { "user": "alice", "time": now() }

// Probe (observe without affecting)
probe "calculation" {
    expensive_computation()
}

// Measure (time a block)
measure "benchmark" {
    process_data()
}
```

## Built-in Functions

### Core
| Function | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `print(x)` | Print without newline |
| `println(x)` | Print with newline |
| `input(prompt)` | Read user input |
| `len(x)` | Length of collection/string |
| `type_of(x)` | Get type name as string |
| `str(x)` | Convert to string |
| `int(x)` | Convert to integer |
| `float(x)` | Convert to float |
| `bool(x)` | Convert to boolean |
| `range(start, end)` | Generate integer range |
| `is_none(x)` | Check if None |
| `is_some(x)` | Check if not None |
| `unwrap(x)` | Unwrap or panic |
| `unwrap_or(x, default)` | Unwrap or use default |

### Collections
| Function | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `map(fn, list)` | Transform each element |
| `filter(fn, list)` | Keep matching elements |
| `reduce(fn, list, init)` | Fold into single value |
| `zip(a, b)` | Pair elements together |
| `enumerate(list)` | Add indices |
| `sorted(list)` | Sort ascending |
| `reversed(list)` | Reverse order |
| `flatten(nested)` | Flatten one level |
| `chunk(list, n)` | Split into chunks |
| `unique(list)` | Remove duplicates |
| `sum(list)` | Sum all elements |

### Math
| Function | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `abs(x)` | Absolute value |
| `min(a, b)` | Minimum |
| `max(a, b)` | Maximum |
| `floor(x)` | Floor division |
| `ceil(x)` | Ceiling |
| `round(x, n)` | Round to n places |
| `sqrt(x)` | Square root |
| `pow(x, n)` | Power |
| `sin(x)`, `cos(x)`, `tan(x)` | Trigonometry |
| `log(x)` | Natural logarithm |
| `clamp(x, lo, hi)` | Clamp to range |

### Math Engine
| Function | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `mean(data)` | Arithmetic mean |
| `median(data)` | Median value |
| `variance(data)` | Population variance |
| `std_dev(data)` | Standard deviation |
| `correlation(x, y)` | Pearson correlation |
| `linear_regression(x, y)` | Slope and intercept |
| `derivative(fn, x)` | Compute f'(x) via AD |
| `gradient(fn, point)` | Compute gradient |
| `bisection(fn, a, b)` | Find root in [a,b] |
| `newton_raphson(fn, x0)` | Newton's method |
| `simpson_integrate(fn, a, b, n)` | Numerical integration |
| `Matrix(data)` | Create matrix |
| `Vector(data)` | Create vector |
| `Interval(lo, hi)` | Create interval |
| `Dual(real, dual)` | Create dual number |

### Crypto Engine
| Function | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `sha256(data)` | SHA-256 hash |
| `sha512(data)` | SHA-512 hash |
| `blake2b(data)` | BLAKE2b hash |
| `hmac_sign(msg, key)` | HMAC signature |
| `hmac_verify(msg, key, sig)` | Verify HMAC |
| `hash_password(pwd)` | PBKDF2 password hash |
| `verify_password(pwd, hash)` | Verify password |
| `random_token(len)` | Secure random hex token |
| `to_base64(data)` | Base64 encode |
| `from_base64(data)` | Base64 decode |
| `to_hex(data)` | Hex encode |
| `from_hex(data)` | Hex decode |
| `lbe_encode(data)` | LBE binary encode |
| `lbe_decode(data)` | LBE binary decode |

### Async Runtime
| Function | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `parallel_map(fn, list)` | Map in parallel |
| `parallel_filter(fn, list)` | Filter in parallel |
| `run_with_timeout(fn, t)` | Execute with timeout |
| `Channel(capacity)` | CSP-style channel |
| `TaskGroup(workers)` | Structured concurrency |

## Standard Library Modules

```lateralus
import stdlib.math         // Mathematical functions
import stdlib.strings      // String utilities
import stdlib.collections  // Advanced data structures
import stdlib.time         // Time and duration
import stdlib.random       // Random generation
import stdlib.science      // Physical constants & conversions
import stdlib.optimize     // Numerical methods
import stdlib.functional   // FP utilities
import stdlib.stats        // Statistical functions
import stdlib.crypto       // Cryptographic operations
import stdlib.linalg       // Linear algebra
import stdlib.os           // File system, paths, process
import stdlib.datetime     // Date/time construction and arithmetic
import stdlib.regex        // Regular expressions
import stdlib.http         // HTTP client
import stdlib.result       // Result/Option monads
import stdlib.iter         // Lazy iterator combinators
import stdlib.json         // JSON parse/encode
import stdlib.io           // File I/O
import stdlib.data         // Data processing
import stdlib.graph        // Graph algorithms
import stdlib.matrix       // Matrix operations
import stdlib.signals      // Signal processing
import stdlib.algorithms   // Sorting, searching
import stdlib.network      // Network utilities
import stdlib.async        // Async primitives
import stdlib.testing      // Test assertions
import stdlib.fmt          // String formatting (v2.2)
import stdlib.csv          // CSV parse/write (v2.2)
import stdlib.uuid         // UUID generation (v2.2)
import stdlib.hash         // Hash functions (v2.2)
import stdlib.base64       // Base64 encode/decode (v2.2)
import stdlib.sort         // Sorting algorithms (v2.3)
import stdlib.set          // Set operations (v2.3)
import stdlib.event        // Event emitter (v2.3)
import stdlib.heap         // Binary heap (v2.4)
import stdlib.deque        // Double-ended queue (v2.4)
import stdlib.trie         // Prefix trie (v2.4)
import stdlib.ini          // INI config parser (v2.4)
import stdlib.lru          // LRU cache (v2.4)
```

## File Extensions

| Extension | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|
| `.ltl` | LATERALUS source code |
| `.ltlc` | Compiled binary format |
| `.ltlml` | LATERALUS Markup Language |
| `.ltasm` | LATERALUS Assembly |

## CLI Commands

```bash
lateralus run <file.ltl>           # Execute a program
lateralus build <file.ltl>         # Build without running
lateralus py <file.ltl>            # Transpile to Python 3
lateralus c <file.ltl>             # Transpile to C99
lateralus c <file.ltl> --freestanding  # C99 freestanding (no libc)
lateralus js <file.ltl>            # Transpile to JavaScript
lateralus wasm <file.ltl>          # Transpile to WebAssembly
lateralus check <file.ltl>         # Type check / lint
lateralus repl                     # Interactive REPL
lateralus repl --enhanced          # Enhanced REPL with :doc/:save/:profile
lateralus ast <file.ltl>           # Print AST
lateralus ir <file.ltl>            # Print IR
lateralus asm <file.ltl>           # Print assembly
lateralus compile <file.ltl>       # Compile to .ltlc
lateralus decompile <file.ltlc>    # Decompile .ltlc
lateralus disasm <file.ltbc>       # Disassemble bytecode
lateralus inspect <file.ltlc>      # Inspect binary
lateralus bench                    # Run micro-benchmarks
lateralus profile <file.ltl>       # Profile compilation
lateralus clean                    # Remove build artifacts
lateralus doc <file.ltlml>         # Render to HTML
lateralus fmt <file.ltl>           # Format code
lateralus lint <file.ltl>          # Lint code
lateralus info                     # Show version and targets
```

